  "text": "Both northern blot analyses and in situ hybridization studies suggest that Fe65 is expressed throughout the murine brain. The pattern of Fe65 expression corresponds to brain regions with the highest density of neurons. This pattern indicates that Fe65 is highly expressed in the regions particularly affected by AD-associated neuropathology, the hippocampus and cortex [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
